1. User-Level Threads (ULT)
Managed by user-level libraries instead of the OS.

Characteristics:
Fast creation
OS not aware of threads
If one thread blocks, entire process may block

2. Kernel-Level Threads (KLT)
Managed directly by the operating system.

Characteristics:
OS schedules threads
Better concurrency
Higher overhead than user threads
Used in systems like Linux and Microsoft Windows.
